ey\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"portugal travel guide douro valley\" class=\"wp-image-55766 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-109x163.jpg 109w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-120x180.jpg 120w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-512x768.jpg 512w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-721x1080.jpg 721w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-961x1440.jpg 961w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-300x450.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-600x899.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1.jpg 1281w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-20x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084925\/douro-valley1-540x810.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><strong>Monsanto to Douro Valley:<\/strong> 3 hours driving. Alternatively, make your way down into the valley by taxi to the town of Covilha. From here, there is a public bus to Peso Regua, taking 3 hours. Be aware that only two buses run per day.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4.jpg\" alt=\"road trip portugal\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"311\" alt=\"road trip portugal\" class=\"wp-image-55772 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-800x552.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-1080x745.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-450x311.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-30x21.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-163x112.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-261x180.jpg 261w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-768x530.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16084955\/douro-valley4-1024x707.jpg 1024w, https