portugal.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><figcaption>Source: Unsplash<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Peso Regua to Braga:<\/strong> 1 hour 20 minutes driving. If using public transport, you will need to go to Porto first and access the bus or train from there. From Porto, Braga can be visited easily by train in just under an hour, with a regular service running throughout the day.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-day-7-9-porto\">Day 7-9: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/porto-things-to-do\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Porto<\/a><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/porto-things-to-do\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Porto<\/a>: Lisbon&#x2019;s much-loved little sibling! Any Portuguese road trip is not complete without spending a few days in this extraordinary city. Walk in the small hillside streets, take the funicular railway, and discover <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/livraria-lello-porto\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Livraria Lello<\/a>; one of the most magical bookstores in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/europe\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Europe<\/a>.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16085430\/porto3-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"portugal travel guide porto\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"portugal travel guide porto\" class=\"wp-image-55828 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/16085430\/porto3-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.co